news.title: Now, consent of only 51% members required for redevelopment of buildings in Navi Mumbai
news.para: "The CIDCO has included a provision that the building can be reconstructed with the consent of only 51 per cent of the members of the housing society instead of the earlier 100 per cent," the town planning authority in Navi Mumbai said.

news.title: Illegal houses on comunidade, government land will be razed: Goa CM
news.para: The state on Wednesday passed the Goa Regularisation of Unauthorised Construction (Amendment) Bill, 2023. Revenue minister Atanasio ‘Babush’ Monserrate said at least 4,800 applications are pending.

news.title: Three times water tariff for builders who construct without PWD nod in Goa
news.para: There is an issue of water not reaching to some of the complexes because the builders did not come to the PWD to check if the department can provide water supply to the complexes, Cabral said during a calling attention motion.

news.title: Truck operators protest against closure of cement plants in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: The two cement plants at Barmana (ACC) and Darlaghat (Ambuja Cements) are closed for the past 35 days, following a dispute over freight charges and operators engaged in carriage of cement and clinkers are on roads.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body reduces fine for delay in updating property transfer records
news.para: The notification states that this is in accordance with provisions of Section 105 1 and 2 of the Punjab Municipal Corporation Act, 1994, which extends the jurisdiction of the municipal corporation to Chandigarh.

news.title: Mysuru civic body registers record revenue collection in current fiscal year
news.para: The MCC has managed to collect Rs 155 crore against its target for 2022-23, and with more than two months left before the end of the fiscal year, the civic agency is confident of collecting the reminder of the funds.

news.title: Over 90 out of 210 illegal colonies in Indore all set to be legalized
news.para: According to Indore collector Ilayaraja T, the administration has taken up the issue of legalizing around 210 illegal colonies and therefore, detailed report of status of its land like encroachment on government land and lack of required permissions including that of T&CP.

news.title: Income tax department continues searches on realty firms in Hyderabad for second day
news.para: The searches were carried out on four real estate firms — Ira Realty Tech Private Limited, Sri Aditya Homes, Oorjita Builders & Developers and CSK Builders — for alleged tax evasion.

news.title: Out of 10,000 buildings, 6,000 asked for safety certificates: Delhi government to HC
news.para: The Delhi government said structural audit of 4655 buildings has been done, while retrofitting is in progress in respect of 89.

news.title: Hidco to auction 7.4-acre plot in South Kolkata
news.para: The starting bid price for the plot has been kept at Rs 125 crore, standing at around Rs 17 crore for each acre. The auction process will be conducted by the Housing Infrastructure Development Corporation (Hidco).

news.title: West Bengal allows government land lessees to opt for ownership, at a price
news.para: The move - allowing outright sale of government-leased land - is expected to boost state coffers and give a fillip to ease of doing business.

news.title: Lenders fix base auction price of Rs 305 crore for Rajesh LifeSpaces' hotel business
news.para: Bidders will have to increase their bids by ₹10 crore in each round with the lowest bids getting eliminated, people familiar with the process said.

news.title: WeWork to cut about 300 jobs globally
news.para: WeWork's long-term lease obligations stood at $15.57 billion at September-end, while some of its tenants are only on short-term leases.

news.title: Geberit sees tough 2023 for Europe's builders after sales dip
news.para: The company, which makes toilets and showers and whose pipes and ceramics are used in renovations and new-build projects, expected raw materials prices to remain flat after they rose sharply during 2022, and its wage bill to rise around 5-6% this year, Buhl also told an analyst call.

news.title: EWS quarters area must be considered single entity: Karnataka government
news.para: It also said the unused residual floor area ratio (FAR) cannot be transferred to the developer, i.e., M/s Maverick Holdings Ltd.
